.TH "ipr_send_hcam" 9 "ipr_send_hcam" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ipr_send_hcam \- Send an HCAM to the adapter.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ipr_send_hcam
.BI "(struct ipr_ioa_cfg *ioa_cfg "  ","
.BI "u8 type "  ","
.BI "struct ipr_hostrcb *hostrcb "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ioa_cfg" 12
ioa config struct
.IP "type" 12
HCAM type
.IP "hostrcb" 12
hostrcb struct
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function will send a Host Controlled Async command to the adapter.
If HCAMs are currently not allowed to be issued to the adapter, it will
place the hostrcb on the free queue.

Return value:
none
